events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander tied his career high with 45 points to lead the Oklahoma City Thunder to a 120-114 victory over the Indiana Pacers on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander ties career high with 45 points as Thunder beat Pacers for ninth straight win

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro hit a 19-foot jumper with 0.5 seconds left Thursday night to give the Miami Heat an 89-88 win over the Orlando Magic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro makes go-ahead jumper with 0.5 seconds left as Heat beat Magic 89-88

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole's 3-pointer with 8.1 seconds remaining lifted the Washington Wizards to a 113-110 victory over the Charlotte Hornets on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poole's 3-pointer with 8.1 seconds left lifts Wizards to a 113-110 win over Hornets

headlines.description: — Jalen Johnson had a career-high 30 points and the Atlanta Hawks rallied from a late 21-point deficit by scoring 50 points in the fourth quarter in a 141-133 win over the Chicago Bulls on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hawks erase 21-point deficit by scoring 50 in the 4th quarter in a 141-133 win over the Bulls

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. had 21 points, 11 rebounds and three blocks, Zach Edey also scored 21 points and grabbed 16 rebounds, and the Memphis Grizzlies set a franchise scoring record in blowing out the skidding Toronto Raptors 155-126 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies set team scoring record in 155-126 rout of Raptors behind Edey and Jackson

headlines.description: — Cam Johnson scored 29 points, Noah Clowney added 20 and the Brooklyn Nets rallied late for a 111-105 victory over the Milwaukee Bucks on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets rally late for 111-105 victory over Bucks, who played again without Antetokounmpo and Lillard

events.name: Houston Rockets at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 30 points in less than 30 minutes on the court, and the Houston Rockets cruised to a 128-111 victory over the hapless, injury-plagued New Orleans Pelicans on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green scores 30 to lead the Rockets to a 128-111 victory over the hapless Pelicans

events.name: Utah Jazz at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Deni Avdija and Shaedon Sharpe each scored 27 points, and Scoot Henderson made a tiebreaking jumper with 0.1 seconds remaining as the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Utah Jazz 122-120 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Henderson hits late jumper, Avdija and Sharpe each score 27 as Trail Blazers beat Jazz 122-120

headlines.description: — Jaden Ivey converted a four-point play with 3 seconds left and the Detroit Pistons rallied past the struggling Sacramento Kings 114-113 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaden Ivey's 4-point play with 3 seconds left rallies Pistons past Kings 114-113
